- Avg response time **â‰¤ 10 minutes**
- Appointment completion rate **â‰¥ 95%**
- Avg patient satisfaction **â‰¥ 4.6**
- Minimum appointment volume threshold met (to avoid low-sample bias)

#### ğŸŸ¡ WATCH
Any of the following conditions:
- Avg response time **10â€“20 minutes**
- Completion rate **88â€“94%**
- Satisfaction **4.2â€“4.5**
- Negative week-over-week trend in **any** KPI (even if still within acceptable range)

WATCH status is intended to surface early signals before performance degrades further.

#### ğŸ”´ NEEDS INTERVENTION
Any of the following conditions:
- Avg response time **> 20 minutes**
- Completion rate **< 88%**
- Satisfaction **< 4.2**
- Sustained negative trend across **2+ weeks**

This category triggers provider outreach and operational follow-up workflows.

---

### Trend detection logic

Trends are evaluated week-over-week using percentage or absolute deltas:

- **Response time:** â‰¥ +20% increase week-over-week
- **Completion rate:** â‰¥ âˆ’5 percentage point drop
- **Satisfaction:** â‰¥ âˆ’0.3 rating drop

Trend signals can escalate a provider to **WATCH** or **NEEDS INTERVENTION** even if absolute thresholds are not yet crossed.

---

### Operational notes
- Classification is recalculated weekly using rolling 7-day or calendar-week windows.
- Providers with very low appointment volume may be excluded or flagged for manual review.
- Thresholds are configurable and stored separately from SQL logic to reflect real-world ops flexibility.

This classification framework allows the system to move beyond reporting and actively support clinical operations decision-making.
